<title>JAPAN: Daiwa Bank (Bank Account) reveals problem loans.</title>
<headline>Daiwa Bank (Bank Account) reveals problem loans.</headline>
<dateline>TOKYO 1997-05-23</dateline>
<text>
<p>Daiwa Bank Ltd has disclosed its restructured loans (in billions of yen unless specified):</p>
<p>					end-Mar 97     end-Mar 96</p>
<p>  Restructured loans	    234.7	    349.8</p>
<p>  Bad loans			 111.7	    122.3</p>
<p>  Non-performing loans	  201.9	    193.1</p>
<p>  Loans to troubled clients   116.7	    141.5</p>
<p>  Total problem loans	   665.0	    806.7</p>
<p>Restructured loans are those on which interest rates have been cut to help corporate restructuring. Bad loans are to bankrupt firms and non-performing are those with interest payments in arrears by six months or more. Loans to troubled clients are mainly to the bank's non-bank affiliates.</p>
</text>
